class SummaryRanges {
    private TreeMap<Integer, int[]> map;

    public SummaryRanges() {
        map = new TreeMap<>();
    }

    public void addNum(int value) {
        if (map.containsKey(value)) return;
        Integer lower = map.lowerKey(value);
        Integer higher = map.higherKey(value);
        boolean connectLeft = lower != null && map.get(lower)[1] + 1 == value;
        boolean connectRight = higher != null && value + 1 == higher;

        if (connectLeft && connectRight) {
            int[] left = map.get(lower);
            int[] right = map.get(higher);
            left[1] = right[1];
            map.remove(higher);
            map.put(lower, left);
        } else if (connectLeft) {
            map.get(lower)[1] = value;
        } else if (connectRight) {
            int[] right = map.get(higher);
            map.remove(higher);
            map.put(value, new int[]{value, right[1]});
        } else {
            map.put(value, new int[]{value, value});
        }
    }

    public int[][] getIntervals() {
        return map.values().toArray(new int[0][]);
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: addNum O(log N), getIntervals O(N)
space complexity: O(N)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a TreeMap to store disjoint intervals keyed by their start; each addNum performs at most two lookups and one merge, yielding logarithmic time. getIntervals returns the sorted values directly.

